<font color="#FF0000">DEATH AND DESTRUCTION</font><br>
<tt>Sat Aug 30 10:40:43 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Only Brothers Understand and Been There<br><br>
HOW TRUE! <br>
It's a VET Thing!<br><br>
666 is the number of men, a silly men who think he knows what death is all about. <br><br>
Death and destruction Ed and Silent Eagle, this one is for you both, in honor of the pain we've shared together..<br><br>
.<br>
.<br>
FOR THOSE WHO KNEW THE SCENT OF HER DISCRETION.<br><br>
You had to taste, smell, sleep, eat and dream with her!<br>
I knew her cousins; pain and agony, suffering and shame. <br>
When she came by, I knew her name. <br>
I knew the scent of her indiscretion!<br>
I had already slept with her; I knew the sour taste from the milk of her breasts.<br>
I laughed at her paleness and this stripped her of her dignity. <br>
I revealed her nakedness and shamed her for her weakness. <br>
She would not spent the night with me in darkness. <br>
She learned fear from my lips when I kissed one night, <br>
She trembled when I embraced and held her tight, <br>
When I whispered to her, O death, where is your sting? <br>
Where is your victory? <br>
She feared to come to me silently, secretly, feared I would not let go and there would be death no more. <br>
She then sends her dark angles to play with my mind <br>
But I knew them as well, and as soon as they spoke, I cut their throats, <br>
Wrapped their thorns in the shadows of the moonless night and when she stepped on them she cried all night.<br>
I left her there, in the jungles of Nam, in the tall trees by the sea, <br>
In rice paddies full of blood, in hooch's absent of love. <br>

